@startuml sequence_deduplication
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Sequence — Deduplication via SQLite UPSERT (L2-014)

participant "HistoryStore" as Store
database "orbit.db\njob_listings" as DB

note over Store, DB
  Deduplication is handled atomically
  by the SQLite ON CONFLICT clause.
  No separate pre-pass needed.
end note

Store -> Store : Normalise each result:\n  company = lower(trim(company))\n  title = lower(trim(title))

Store -> DB : INSERT INTO job_listings (..., status='New', ...)\nON CONFLICT (company, title) DO UPDATE SET\n  status = CASE\n    WHEN excluded.status = 'Applied' THEN 'Applied'\n    ELSE 'Seen'\n  END,\n  last_seen_date = date('now'),\n  scan_run_id = excluded.scan_run_id

note right of DB
  New listings → status = 'New'
  Re-seen listings → status = 'Seen'
  Applied listings → status unchanged
end note

DB --> Store : rows inserted or updated

Store -> DB : SELECT\n  SUM(CASE WHEN status='New' THEN 1 END) AS new_count,\n  SUM(CASE WHEN status='Seen' THEN 1 END) AS seen_count,\n  SUM(CASE WHEN status='Applied' THEN 1 END) AS applied_count\nFROM job_listings\nWHERE scan_run_id = ?

DB --> Store : DeduplicationResult counts
Store --> Store : return DeduplicationResult

@enduml
